<TITLE> Ashraf recovering from surgery </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 14 (bdnews24.com)  LGRD minister Syed Ashraful Islam was recovering from minor surgery at LabAid Hospital Saturday. "The operation was successful. He asked all to pray for his quick recovery," personal assistant Syed Toffazal Hossain said. Ashraf, who was admitted around 11am, underwent laparoscopy colorectal surgery in the afternoon, hospital spokesperson Mesbah Azad told bdnews24.com. Starting around 12:30pm, the operation was over by 2pm, hospital spokesperson Mesbah Azad told bdnews24.com. General surgeon Prof Khademul Islam performed the surgery. "The patient will remain in the postoperative ward for fours before returning to his cabin," Azad said. The Awami League leader is expected to remain in hospital for two days altogether, he said. bd
